Named after the unfortunate cruiser that served to build it's main power core, the Hammer of Retribushun is Captain Hardbak's and his kommandos trusty flagship. Half heavy carrier, half dreadnot, it was on all battles would said Hardbak, loaded with enough heavy fire power, strike bommas and unstable torpedoes to aggressively support greenskins assaults.

**This pack includes :**
- 1 battleship ;
- separate parts for easier printing ;
- 2x custom weapon modules (heavy guns, launch bays) ;
- the prow has a blank spot to fit a looted weapon.

The ship is roughly 125mm long and can be used to represent the ork battleship Gorbag's Revenge or serve as a base for a large ork capital ship.

_ The files are unsupported and come with a slot for 3mm or 1/8 inch stem.
_ The bases I like to use are free and can be found here :
https://www.myminifactory.com/object/3d-print-soul-forge-studio-ship-bases-165370
_This pack is available to anyone so please don't sell, reupload or redistribute the files/models.

**_My ork ships are based on or use free parts from Styxx83's excellent ork fleet, please take a few minutes to browse his work. All the original weapon inserts and other parts can be found on his battleship if needed :**
https://www.thingiverse.com/styxx83/designs

A version with a base attached and a pre-supported version is included in the download.

I recommend printing on a resin printer.

Ork Savage Gunship for the long out-of-production wargame Battlefleet Gothic.

The model by jimjimjimmyjim (from Battlefleet Gothic Armada 2) didn't have any guns, so I mixed in some other big guns and scaled them appropriately.

I have removed a lot of small gubbins from the original mesh, as it was far to small to print properly. This prints fine, as the picture clearly illustrates.

The cover picture shows two printed Savages along original Savages from the game.

2020-05-11: Added a pre-supported Chitubox file for easy printing of 3 Savages. Note: These Savages have stands permanently attached to them.

Ork spaceship that can be used as a Kill Kroozer or a Terror Ship in the long out-of-production game Battlefleet Gothic.

I did the following remix of the source material:
- extracted the Ork Battleship from the source
- scaled it to 100 mm length
- removed the geometry inside the model

Many of the details are obviously too tiny for most printers, so you'll probably need to do some pruning before slicing and printing it at this scale.

Note: I did not design this model. I think it was extracted from Battlefleet Gothic: Armada 2.

Updates 2020-05-15:
- I updated the title to "Ork Kroozer", as it is labeled as such in the game.
- I have fixed up the model extensively. I have removed a lot of antennae and small gubbins that wouldn't print properly at the proper scale for the board game.
- I have scaled the model down to about 7 cm, which is the same size as the original metal Kroozers.
- I have added a version with a small base attached. This is meant to be printed in one piece.
- I have added a pre-supported file of the kroozer with small base. Both the STL and Chitubox file is available.
